    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A thematic, dashboard-style single-page application. The structure guides the user from a high-level overview to detailed financial performance and risk analysis, using interactive components like stat cards, dynamic charts controlled by buttons, and tabbed sections. This non-linear structure was chosen to make the dense financial report more digestible and engaging, allowing users to explore data based on their interests (e.g., performance vs. risk) rather than following the report's rigid format. The core narrative—aggressive growth balanced by VW's strategic support—is highlighted upfront for immediate context. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Data from the report is translated into interactive visualizations to achieve specific communication goals. For example, 'Receita & Lucro' (Goal: Show growth) uses a combo bar/line chart (Method: Chart.js/Canvas) for efficient comparison. 'Risco de Liquidez' (Goal: Show pressure) uses a multi-line chart to visualize the closing gap between cash and short-term debt. Risk categories are organized into tabs (Method: HTML/JS) to reduce cognitive load. This approach pairs quantitative data with concise textual explanations, all updated interactively, ensuring clarity and user engagement without using SVG or Mermaid. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
